Subject: [PATCH 1/2] =?UTF-8?q?feat(dream):=20wire=20the=20=C2=A74=20accep?=
 =?UTF-8?q?tance=20gates=20(a)-(f)=20+=20populate=20DreamQaProbe=20(#2545)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The dreaming pass shipped phases 1-6 but the §4 acceptance gates that make a
pass anti-vacuous were never implemented, and DreamQaProbe was a dead model:
migrated, but never instantiated, populated, or replayed. A lossy / delete-only
/ no-op consolidation was never caught.

New module teatree.loops.dream.gates implements the six gates, each with an
anti-vacuous test proven in both directions:

- (a) retention: every probe answerable before the pass is still answerable
  after it (a delete-only pass that drops an answer fails).
- (b) interference: the prior-session probe pass-rate must not regress.
- (c) consolidation-actually-happened: net size reduced OR schema count grew OR
  clusters were recorded, AND every pruned index line has a confirmed durable
  home (a no-op pass fails; an unhomed prune fails).
- (d) index-budget: MEMORY.md back under its line/byte load-warning threshold.
- (e) monotonicity: two passes over a stable corpus must not lower the
  retention pass-rate.
- (f) no-loss audit: every archived entry records a source + a destination that
  actually exists (restorable).

DreamQaProbe is now POPULATED: persist_probe_results seeds one probe per memory
(keyed on a signature line), replays it via an injectable, deterministic
LLM-free answerer, and records each outcome idempotently on probe_key,
accumulating pass/run counts and marking re-recorded probes is_prior_session so
the next pass has a baseline.

Wired into the dream command: the cron snapshots each memory dir BEFORE and
AFTER the file-side phases, runs run_acceptance_pass per dir, and gates the
DreamRunMarker on the report. A failing gate marks the pass
attempted-not-succeeded (staleness keeps firing) rather than stamping success.
The command gate-gating is mutation-proven: ignoring the verdict turns the
wiring tests RED.

Open questions and assumptions:
- Probe answerability is a deterministic signature-line substring match against
  the memory set + index (assumed; the answerer is injectable so an LLM answerer
  can replace it without touching the gates).
- Gate (c) treats clusters_recorded > 0 as a consolidation-happened signal so a
  cross-link/reindex-only maintenance pass (which grows the on-disk file set) is
  not failed when distillation landed rules in the DB ledger (assumed).
- Index budget thresholds: 900 lines / 256KB (assumed load-warning floors;
  generous regression alarms, not hard caps).
