@@ -77,7 +77,7 @@ ## 4. Domain Models
 
 Five core lifecycle models in `teatree.core.models/`, all FSM-driven (`django-fsm`): **Ticket**, **Worktree**, **Session**, **Task**, **TaskAttempt**. Around them, supporting rows under the same package: `BotPing`, `ConsolidatedMemory`/`DreamQaProbe`/`DreamRunMarker` (memory-consolidation, below), `DailyDigestThread`/`DailyDigestMessage`, `DbApproval`, `DeferredQuestion`, `EvalRunRecord`/`EvalScenarioResult` (eval-run ledger), `SessionAuditRecord` (eval audit layer), `HonestyEscalation`, `IncomingEvent`, `IntentClassification`, `LandscapeArtifact` (the intake landscape survey the planner consumes, below), `LivePostApproval`, `LocalStackQueueItem`, `LocalStackReaperMarker`, `Loop` (DB-configured autonomous loop — name, exactly one of prompt-FK/script, run_in_sub_agent/description/overlay, nullable delay, enabled, §5.6), `LoopLease`, `LoopState` (durable per-loop control plane, §5.6), `MergeClear`, `OnBehalfApproval`, `OutboundClaim` (drift verifier), `PendingChatInjection`, `Prompt`/`PromptVersion` (first-class reusable prompt with templated `params` + edit-history snapshots, the `Loop.prompt` FK target and the `/prompts` trigger, §5.6), `PullRequest`, `RedCardSignal`, `ReplyDispatch`, `ReviewAssignment`, `ReviewLoop`/`ReviewLoopRound` (the bounded author↔reviewer ping-pong FSM + its round-leg slot, §5.6), `ReviewRequestPost`, `ReviewVerdict`, `ScannedBroadcast`, `SelfImproveFiring`, `SessionHandover`, `TicketTransition`, `WorktreeEnvOverride`. Every row name above is cited by name from §5.6, §17.1, §17.4, or §4 prose.
 
-**Memory-consolidation data layer ([#1933](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/1933)).** Three durable rows back the idle-time "dreaming" pass that clusters session feedback and distils each cluster into one imperative rule. `ConsolidatedMemory` is the consolidation ledger (the DB row is canonical state + audit trail; a rendered topic file is the output), idempotency-anchored on a sha256 `cluster_key` and owning its status ladder `CANDIDATE → VERIFIED → PROMOTED` (plus `SUPERSEDED`/`EXPIRED`); it refuses an uncited rule, refuses to silently expire a BINDING row, and gates index-line pruning on a terminal status with a recorded durable home. **Pass 2 — memory→fix ([#2426](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2426)).** A `disposition` ladder (`UNTRIAGED → USER_SPECIFIC_KEEP | (CORE_GAP_NEEDS_TICKET → TICKETED → RESOLVED_RETIRED)`) makes the ledger a queue that DRAINS, not a pile that grows: a generic/teatree-core memory is a confession that core has a workflow gap, so `teatree.loops.dream.promote_memory` triages each untriaged row (injected `MemoryClassifier`, default the `durable_destination`-hint one — a home under teatree's own skills/source/scripts/BLUEPRINT is core-generic, anything else stays user-specific memory), files a deduped `needs-triage` teatree backlog ticket for each core gap (`cluster_key`-keyed marker; banned-term + bare-reference scanned so the public-repo body never leaks; records `ticket_url`), and retires the prose (`RESOLVED_RETIRED`, archived) once the linked ticket closes. A BINDING row is never retired. Pass 2 auto-files the *ticket* (durable, reversible) but never auto-implements; it is **default OFF** behind the `[loops.dream] memory_promote` / `T3_DREAM_MEMORY_PROMOTE` toggle, so an unflagged pass never triages or files. `DreamQaProbe` is the schema for the retention/interference/monotonicity QA corpus, but the § 4 acceptance gates that would populate and replay it are **not yet wired** — the model is migrated and unused, so no gate runs during a pass today ([#2545](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2545)). `DreamRunMarker` is the staleness marker keyed on the success timestamp (a run that keeps failing stays stale). `t3 dream run` (manual) and `t3 dream tick` (cadence-gated cron, ~04:00) take a `dream-tick` `LoopLease` and run the distillation engine (`teatree.loops.dream.engine.run_consolidation`), stamping `DreamRunMarker` only on a clean pass; `--dry-run` writes nothing. Engine v1 covers phases 1–3 (rank a bounded extract → an injected `Distiller` clusters by root cause → upsert by `cluster_key`, rejecting any uncited/hallucinated cluster and never overwriting a BINDING rule); the injected-distiller seam keeps the pass testable, and an SDK failure propagates rather than laundering into a fake success. **Phases 4–6 are LIVE** ([#1933](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/1933) § 6): the cron runs three memory-file phases over the discovered `~/.claude` memory dirs, each fault-isolated in its own try/except so one phase (or one dir) failing never crashes the tick or stops the others, and each LIVE by default behind its own two-layer kill-switch (`[loops.dream] <phase>` toml / `T3_DREAM_<PHASE>` env, first match wins). The file-side phases run independently of the transcript extract, so they fire even on a 0-transcript-member pass (which stays attempted-not-succeeded for consolidation, but still re-indexes/decays the on-disk memory set; [#2547](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2547)). **Phase 4** (`teatree.loops.dream.cross_link`) appends symmetric `[[name]]` wiki-links between related memories — related when their significant-token Jaccard clears a deterministic floor (no model) — and is idempotent (a re-run on an unchanged set adds nothing). **Phase 5** (`teatree.loops.dream.reindex`) regenerates `MEMORY.md` as one ≤200-char line per memory (deduped, filename-stable, content stays in the topic file), byte-identical on a no-change re-run. **Phase 6** (`teatree.loops.dream.decay`) ages a memory out by ARCHIVING it (moved to `<memory_dir>/archive/` with a provenance header, never deleted) — gated by a NON-VACUOUS retention guard that retains a memory that is EITHER fresh (mtime within the window) OR still referenced (another live memory or the index `[[name]]`-links it); only a memory that is BOTH old AND unreferenced is archived, and a guard-disabled probe proves the guard has teeth. All three accept an explicit `memory_dir` and never touch the real `~/.claude` under test. **Phase 3b** ([#2346](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2346)) closes the drift → live-eval loop: `teatree.loops.dream.eval_proposer` maps each grounded cluster to an eval CANDIDATE in a JSONL review queue, then `teatree.loops.dream.promote` PROMOTES it to a real `under_load` scenario (`evals/scenarios/promoted_drift.yaml` + `_pass`/`_fail` replay fixtures) — the artifacts the deterministic replay gate and the weekly metered lane run unchanged. The nightly `tick` requests proposals **LIVE by default** (the `[loops.dream] propose_evals` / `T3_DREAM_PROPOSE_EVALS` kill-switch flips it off). Promotion is auto but gated by a **non-bypassable anti-vacuity guard** (`promote.guard_can_fail`): it runs the real grader (`teatree.eval.report.evaluate`) against a synthesised drift-recommitting transcript and promotes only when that verdict is FAIL (the matchers have teeth) AND a compliant transcript grades PASS (not a tautology); a candidate whose grader cannot fail is rejected — no file written. The guard is deterministic; live metered grading of a promoted scenario lands with the weekly Agent-SDK lane. **Phase 3b LLM derivation** ([#2447](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2447)) is the richer, **default-OFF** follow-up to the fixed-matcher `promote`: `teatree.loops.dream.llm_eval_proposer` runs an injected LLM synthesizer that turns a grounded candidate plus its cited transcript slice into a COMPLETE `under_load` `EvalSpec` — a pollution preamble saturated to the documented ~28k-char envelope floor, discriminating positive + negative matchers, and a judge rubric — parsed through the real loader and gated by a **candidate-derived** teeth check (`teatree.loops.dream._teeth_check.teeth_check_against_candidate`): it synthesises the `_fail`/`_pass` transcripts FROM the candidate's OWN cited drift and compliant tool-call shapes and grades both through the suite's real grader (`teatree.eval.report.evaluate`), DROPPING a spec whose matchers do not reject the candidate's own cited drift (or reject its compliant shape as a tautology) — proving the matchers target the SPECIFIC drift the candidate describes, not `promote`'s fixed session.py-edit transcripts. Even a proven spec is never autonomously committed to `evals/scenarios`: `stage_derived_evals` writes a staging `derived_evals.yaml` a human / standing core-maker ratifies via a PR. The phase is OFF unless the `[loops.dream] derive_evals` / `T3_DREAM_DERIVE_EVALS` toggle is set, so an unflagged pass is byte-identical. The `dream` mini-loop is registered `off_live_tick` (driven only by its own cron); `t3 doctor` surfaces the 48h staleness alarm.
