From 8aec53bdf8763c1601c4df1cf4c2e5f7452e4efb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 12:23:48 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix(dream): use apps.get_model for ConsolidatedMemory
 count (no deferred core import)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The new _ledger_schema_count helper used a function-scoped
`from teatree.core.models import ConsolidatedMemory`, which pushed the
intra-core deferred-import ratchet from 188 to 189 and failed
test_count_does_not_exceed_frozen. Switch to the AppRegistry-safe
apps.get_model("core", "ConsolidatedMemory") lookup — the same
tach-invisible pattern managers.py uses — so the edge stops hiding an
intra-core cycle from tach and the count returns to the frozen 188.
The §4 acceptance gates and DreamQaProbe population are untouched.
---
 src/teatree/core/management/commands/dream.py | 9 +++++----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/teatree/core/management/commands/dream.py b/src/teatree/core/management/commands/dream.py
index ce0acf0471..f4fb66f57a 100644
--- a/src/teatree/core/management/commands/dream.py
+++ b/src/teatree/core/management/commands/dream.py
